    "2021; Huang et al. 2021) and hybrid loss (Nichol et al.",
    "2022; Cheng et al. 2022) are proposed to improve likelihood training.",
    "Almost all diffusion models use the Convolutional U-Net (Ronneberger et al. 2015) as their backbone, but Peebles and Xie (2023); Ma et al.",
    "(2024) introduced Transformer to diffusion models, further enhancing their generation capabilities and resulting in the recent high-performance video generation model Sora Liuet al.",
    "The diffusion model assumes that the data exists in Euclidean space, which initially only handles continuous data such as images."
